reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Product is good, the Dodge light housing might not be
reviews.reviewText: ModitoFix Map Dome Light Lens Clear Cover Interior Roof White Led Blubs kit for Dodge Ram -- I got this for my 2008 Dodge Ram 5500. The original lenses were slightly yellowed and bulbs were not bright enough. When I popped out the original lenses and bulbs (without any problems) I find that the old lenses look exactly like the new lenses. They were not yellowed after all. Dim light problem was with the bulbs alone. When I pressed the first new LED into the contacts, I heard and felt the plastic housing crack. Looked and decided to leave it until later because it will still work. Carefully installed the other bulb. First new lens that I tried to install, one of the lens pivots tabs broke off. Carefully applied some pressure on the other tabs with my finger to test them and another one broke off. I didn't even want to think about buying anther dome light/display housing so I set about figuring how to repair it. When I removed the housing I found it was a cheap thin brittle plastic. The tabs would not glue back on and hold. So with my Dremel, pliers, some plastic epoxy, and a wire coat hanger I designed and installed new axels for the lens pivot points. Coated all the cracks, broken points and probably going to break points with epoxy. The housing is now better than original and everything works including the brighter LEDs. The 5 minute job ended up taking about 3 hours work and two days of curing time. So the lesson here for you is these new lenses and LEDs will work and look great. However, think twice before trying to replace the dome lights in your cheap plastic Dodge housing.

They fit find although when doing the bulb I noticed that the clips that hold the ends of the bulb were a little loose and did not give a good connection. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A mod worth doing - Get these!
reviews.reviewText: I have a 20+ year old Dodge Ram. The interior lights were halogen, so they had a dull yellowish glow to them. I wanted to brighten it up inside and see if I could get more lumens using LED bulbs. The two replacement lenses come with the bulbs which worked great - no LED ghosting.I did run into a problem, as some of the plastic is older, the switch that toggles the lights on/off had come loose from its housing. To be able to manually turn the lights on and off by pressing the lens, I had to use super glue to secure the switch back to a sturdy position. I spent about 30 minutes on that, otherwise this would have only taken 10 minutes to upgrade the bulbs and replace the new lenses.It’s an upgrade worth doing though, it looks great!

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect fit for 2004 dodge ram
reviews.reviewText: For 10 years we have been without interior lights in the truck. Dome light fix requires a new motherboard (no thanks), and the map light switches broke years ago. Tried popping bulbs in and out, but that got old after awhile. Finally decided to purchase new switches, bulbs, and lenses (the old bulbs and lenses are long ago lost). These bulbs and lenses fit perfectly. Now that the switches are fixed too, we have light in the cab. I love how bright the LED bulbs are. Would definitely recommend.
